The Latin epiCS, therefore, which re- sulted from this tendency were far from being national in tone. They might have a beauty and romance of their own, but it was the beauty of a hothouse plant, not of an indigenous growth. Thus it was that when virgil stepped into the field, Rome had no great narrative poem that could be regarded as satisfying the ideals of patriot and artist alike.
